34
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Planck's constant being equal to 1, that's something that's permissible to do.

35
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:52,000
And it's just units in which the uncertainty principle says that the product of the uncertainty of position times the uncertainty of momentum is equal to one unit, one unit of something.

36
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Namely, one unit of action.

37
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
But C equals h-bar equals 1.

38
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:01,000
But we won't fiddle around or try to simplify Newton's constant for a moment.

39
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:10,000
If, oh, if you set C equals h-bar equal to 1, then there's only one unit that you have to specify.

40
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:14,000
You can either take it to be a length or a mass.

41
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
And a mass is an inverse length.

42
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
A mass is an inverse length.

43
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
I'll just remind you of that.

44
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,000
I'll just remind you why that is.

45
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:30,000
It's the fact that energy, which is the same as mass, all you need to do is to write an equation.

46
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Find some equation for energy and look at the various dimensions and we'll see what happens.

47
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
All right.

48
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:48,000
So energy, for example, in quantum mechanics, energy is given by Planck's constant divided by the wavelength times C.

49
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Where lambda is the wavelength of a photon, for example.

50
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:56,000
This would be a connection between the energy of a photon and its wavelength.

51
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:04,000
We're not using it for anything except to say what the relationship between the energy, between the mass units and length units are.

52
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Now, this is not mass.

53
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
To make it mass, I think we have to divide it by C squared.

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,000
